65
00:04:35,090 --> 00:04:36,710
Go into the forest!
I'll cover your back!

66
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:37,810
Okay!

67
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:42,430
Go left! We'll head to the mountain!

68
00:04:42,430 --> 00:04:43,240
Got it!

69
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,590
We'll shake them off somehow!

70
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:47,790
It'd take us until night
to finish fighting them!

71
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:50,380
These snow mountain
animals really are tough!

72
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:51,780
We're at a disadvantage.

73
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:54,940
Don't!

74
00:04:57,810 --> 00:05:00,560
Idiot! I told you not to attack!

75
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:02,580
Just leave them to me!

76
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:03,680
Sorry...

77
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,280
This isn't a joke!

78
00:05:06,050 --> 00:05:07,950
Sanji! We can go up from here!

79
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:09,550
Good! Go on ahead!

80
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:11,920
Heave-ho!

81
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:22,600
--They're coming!
--You don't need to egg them on!

82
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:25,720
Anyway, run! To the top of the mountain!

83
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,510
It's getting strong...

84
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:32,680
Nami-san, please be okay...

85
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:37,940
Who in the world are you guys?

86
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,690
Who are we...?

87
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:42,140
It's too reckless for just the 6 of you

88
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:45,050
to travel in the Grand Line
without a doctor.

89
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:46,560
We're pirates.

90
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,550
That's why you guys
pointed guns at us, right?

91
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,760
Well, we may be a small group...

92
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:55,060
but as long as I, Brave Warrior
of the Sea, am with them,

93
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,830
there's no need to worry.

94
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:57,870
I see...

95
00:05:57,870 --> 00:06:01,170
But it's true that we do want a doctor.

96
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:05,010
I was hoping to find someone
like that on this island, but...

97
00:06:05,010 --> 00:06:08,800
I didn't expect that there was only one
doctor, a witch living in that castle...

98
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,550
It's a strange combination...

99
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:16,890
It seems that you guys're different
from the pirates that we think of.

100
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:18,870
Dalton-san!

101
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,610
Dalton-san!

102
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:21,460
Gotta bow...

103
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:22,980
Oh, hi.

104
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:26,000
I heard that you're looking for Dr. Kureha?

105
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,100
Yes, that's right, but the
sick person has already...

106
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,250
I heard that she's in our neighboring town,

107
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:33,250
Cocoaweed, right now.

108
00:06:35,810 --> 00:06:37,210
What?!

109
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:39,630
Then they passed each other?!

110
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:50,350
Hey, owner. We've had enough already!

111
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:53,430
Your kid's voice is so loud
that I can't stand it!

112
00:06:53,690 --> 00:06:55,200
Ah, I'm sorry.

113
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:59,340
Hey, Tamachibi, what's wrong?
Does it hurt somewhere?

114
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,010
If you just keep crying,
I won't know what's wrong.

115
00:07:03,010 --> 00:07:04,780
You're disturbing customers.

116
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:08,320
Tamachibi! Say something!

117
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:10,450
If you don't stop crying,
I'll lock you out!

118
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:14,740
--It's the witch!
--Shh! She can her you!

119
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:15,740
--Scary...
--Shh! She can her you!

120
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:18,460
She's with that creepy monster again...

121
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,420
Hey! That's enough!

122
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:28,550
Well well... What a mean father...

123
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:31,440
If a child keeps crying,

124
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:34,010
he's signaling that
something's wrong with his body.

125
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:38,440
Stay there, Chopper.

126
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,390
Sorry to interrupt...

127
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:46,860
Dr...

128
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,160
Are you kids happy?

129
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,410
Dr. Kureha!

130
00:07:55,550 --> 00:07:57,290
My secret to staying young?

131
00:07:57,290 --> 00:07:58,370
No! We didn't ask that!

132
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:01,870
I still can't believe
she's a 140 year old hag...

133
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:05,000
I'm still 139!

134
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,720
Shall I make it better?

135
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,590
Hm?! Make what better?

136
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,970
He isn't sick or anything.

137
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,640
Are you... a doctor?

138
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:23,110
Well then, shall we go, Chopper?

139
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:26,070
Wait!

140
00:08:29,490 --> 00:08:31,730
I'm sorry. It was my mistake.

141
00:08:33,140 --> 00:08:36,670
Since I heard that the doctor
came down the mountain yesterday,

142
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:40,040
I thought she wouldn't
come down for a while.

143
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:43,060
Don't worry about it.
It's not your fault.

144
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:46,100
The issue here is Luffy and
Sanji's abnormal physical strength.

145
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:48,870
Even if we go after them
in the snow mountain now,

146
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:50,760
